# Maintainer / contributor collaboration (Cursor)

## Roles

- **Maintainer**: owns release discipline, sensitive operator context under **gitignored** `docs/private/`, and merge/release policy per `AGENTS.md` / `CONTRIBUTING.md`.
- **Contributor**: follows the same `AGENTS.md` and tracked docs; uses **feature branches** and **PRs** to the canonical repo (or PR from fork → upstream).

## Identity

- **Git** `user.name` / `user.email` on each machine identify **commit authors**. The assistant does **not** reliably know the human at the keyboard unless the operator states it in chat.
- Do **not** assume maintainer-only tasks (homelab secrets, study cadence, private notes) apply to a contributor session unless the operator says so.

## Where to look

- Human-readable workflow + copy-paste Git commands + suggested Cursor prompts: **`docs/COLLABORATION_TEAM.pt_BR.md`** (full) and **`docs/COLLABORATION_TEAM.md`** (link stub).
- Global agent contract: **`AGENTS.md`**. Contribution flow: **`CONTRIBUTING.md`**.

## Tracked vs private

- **Never** put real secrets, LAN IPs, or personal maintainer-only chores into **tracked** files to “help” a contributor; use issues/PRs and public docs instead.
- **`docs/private/`** is workspace-only / gitignored from GitHub per `AGENTS.md` — contributors may not have the same tree; do not require it for routine product work.
